contentrichtext.text: {{wiktionary|VG}} '''VG''' may refer to: * [[Vicar General]], the principal deputy of a Christian bishop * [[Victoria Gardens (shopping center)]], an open-air retail center in [[Rancho Cucamonga]], [[California]]. * [[Nissan VG engine]] * [[VG Airlines]] (defunct Belgian airline) * ''[[VG Cats]]'', a webcomic * [[VG (nerve agent)]], the NATO designation for a chemical weapon agent, a.k.a. Amiton * [[VG (shop)]], a now-defunct chain of retail stores in the United Kingdom * [[British Virgin Islands]], ISO 3166-1 country code ** [[.vg]], the country code top-level domain for the British Virgin Islands * ''[[Verdens Gang]]'', a Norwegian newspaper * [[VG-lista]], the official Norwegian singles chart * Vegetable Glycerine, otherwise known as [[Glycerol]] '''VG''', as a symbol, may refer to: * VG, the NYSE symbol for [[Vonage]] * VG, the IATA airline designator for [[VLM Airlines]] * ''[[Variable Geo]]'', a series of hentai fighter arcade games * [[Vein of Galen]], a blood vessel in the cerebrum * ''[[Victory Gundam]]'', short for ''Kidou Senshi Victory Gundam'', a 1993 anime series * [[Video game]] * VG is a grade in the Swedish grade system. * ''[[Világgazdaság]]'', a Hungarian economic daily * [[Volksgrenadier]], a special kind of German infantry * [[Volume group]], a feature of the Linux computer operating system * ''[[Vanguard: Saga of Heroes]]'', an MMORPG computer game released in 2007 * "vestigial wings" (VG), a gene in ''[[Drosophila melanogaster]]'' genetics * Very Good, as in [[Goodness and value theory]] '''Vg''' may stand for: *[[Virgin]], in the Christian Church; when the term ''Vg.'' follows the name of a Christian saint it denotes that the saint was a virgin. {{disambiguation}}
